            <br>
            <h3 align="center" style="font-weight: bold">The man who lost 68 kgs thanks to his college professor</h3>
            <p class='text'>When Joey Morganelli was 16 years old, he watched his father die of a heart attack right in front of him, only three years after losing his mother to cancer. Looking for a way to cope with such tragedy and loss, he turned
              to food. By the time he graduated high school, he weighed 181 kgs.</p>
            <p class='text'>Then he started eating nutritious, home-cooked meals instead of fast food. He eventually grew more devoted, switching to a vegan diet, and losing 68 kgs by mid-2018.</p>
            <p class='text'>He said on Instagram that while losing weight is difficult, facing yourself and dealing with the reasons that led you to overeat in the first place is far more difficult. He wrote, "Give yourself a fair fight and take off
              your blindfold." "It'll take you someplace you never imagined you could go."</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-5 mb-5 item-center">
          <img class="item" src="/assets/img/success_story/2.jpg">
          <p class="item">Joey Morganelli/Instagram</p>
        </div><!-- End second story -->

        <!-- Third story -->
        <div class="col-md-5 item-center">
          <img class="item" src="/assets/img/success_story/3.jpg">
          <p class="item">Mary Jane O'Toole/Instagram</p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-7 mb-5 content-green-bg">
          <div class="icon-box" data-aos-delay="200">
            <br>
            <h3 align="center" style="font-weight: bold">The bride who lost 61 kgs and wore her dream wedding dress</h3>
            <p>Mary Jane O'Toole couldn't have been happier when she and her longtime partner got engaged in 2016. However, at 128 kgs, selecting a wedding gown was a difficult task.</p>
            <p>"I didn't want to buy a plus-size wedding dress, because they cost way more than straight sizes," O'Toole told People in April. "I felt like I was paying this fat tax—I didn't have the ability to buy affordable clothes because I was
              bigger."</p>
            <p>O'Toole shed 34 kgs in the first year and another 11 kgs after the couple started exercising together. She had shed a total of 61 kgs by the time the wedding came around early this year, and she was able to walk down the aisle in the
              dress of her dreams.</p>
          </div>
        </div><!-- End third story -->

        <!-- Fourth story -->
        <div class="col-md-7 icon-boxes">
