            <h3 align="center" style="font-weight: bold">The teen who lost 80 kgs and fell in love with fitness</h3>
            <p class='text'>Hunter Croteau had to see the doctor to learn that he weighed 166 kg because his home scale was no longer capable of weighing him. Croteau plunged himself into a healthy diet after graduating from high school, with the help of his family. However, after two weeks, he slipped off the wagon.</p>
            <p class='text'>Croteau told Yahoo! Lifestyle in July, "I knew lying in bed that night that I wasn't going to go back on the diet the next morning, and I needed to undertake a radical move." His doctor recommended a sleeve gastrectomy, which eliminates about 80% of the stomach and so restricts the amount of food a person can eat.</p>
            <p class='text'>Croteau decided to have the surgery, even though he was "extremely nervous" going into the operation. After the surgery Croteau became very interested in the science of gymnasiums and have good routine and now aims to be a professional trainer. With discipline, effort and proper diet we can achieve our goals "Sometimes all you have to do is believe and you are halfway there!"</p>
